"d9f1264c-3c97-4116-a4a7-7a772c32625b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/nodo/work/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a1a5082c-34f9-4b1f-af70-2870eacef097\",\"version\":\"2.1.68\",\"gitBranch\":\"nodo/external-plugins\",\"slug\":\"cozy-wandering-wall\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_013GUfhRVZY7DkxN95ruwXD2\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# External Agent Plugin Protocol\\n     2→\\n     3→## Overview\\n     4→\\n     5→The Entire CLI supports external agent plugins — standalone binaries that implement the Agent interface via a subcommand-based protocol over stdin/stdout. This allows third-party agents to integrate with the CLI without modifying the main repository.\\n     6→\\n     7→## Discovery\\n     8→\\n     9→The CLI discovers external agents by scanning `$PATH` for executables matching the pattern `entire-agent-<name>`. For example, `entire-agent-cursor` would register as the \\\"cursor\\\" agent.\\n    10→\\n    11→- Binaries whose `<name>` conflicts with an already-registered built-in agent are skipped.\\n    12→- Discovery runs once during CLI initialization (before building the hooks command tree).\\n    13→- The binary must be executable and respond to the `info` subcommand.\\n    14→\\n    15→## Environment\\n    16→\\n    17→Every subcommand invocation sets:\\n    18→\\n    19→| Variable | Description |\\n    20→|---|---|\\n    21→| `ENTIRE_REPO_ROOT` | Absolute path to the git repository root |\\n    22→| `ENTIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION` | Protocol version (`1`) |\\n    23→\\n    24→The working directory is set to the repository root.\\n    25→\\n    26→## Communication Model\\n    27→\\n    28→- **Subcommand-based:** Each Agent interface method maps to a CLI subcommand.\\n    29→- **JSON over stdin/stdout:** Structured data uses JSON. Transcripts use raw bytes.\\n    30→- **Stateless:** Each invocation is independent — no persistent connection.\\n    31→- **Exit codes:** `0` = success, non-zero = error. Error messages go to stderr.\\n    32→\\n    33→## Subcommands\\n    34→\\n    35→### Always Required\\n    36→\\n    37→#### `info`\\n    38→\\n    39→Returns agent metadata and declared capabilities.\\n    40→\\n    41→**Arguments:** None\\n    42→\\n    43→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n    44→\\n    45→```json\\n    46→{\\n    47→  \\\"protocol_version\\\": 1,\\n    48→  \\\"name\\\": \\\"cursor\\\",\\n    49→  \\\"type\\\": \\\"Cursor\\\",\\n    50→  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\\\",\\n    51→  \\\"is_preview\\\": true,\\n    52→  \\\"protected_dirs\\\": [\\\".cursor\\\"],\\n    53→  \\\"hook_names\\\": [\\\"session-start\\\", \\\"session-end\\\", \\\"stop\\\"],\\n    54→  \\\"capabilities\\\": {\\n    55→    \\\"hooks\\\": true,\\n    56→    \\\"transcript_analyzer\\\": true,\\n    57→    \\\"transcript_preparer\\\": false,\\n    58→    \\\"token_calculator\\\": false,\\n    59→    \\\"text_generator\\\": false,\\n    60→    \\\"hook_response_writer\\\": false,\\n    61→    \\\"subagent_aware_extractor\\\": false\\n    62→  }\\n    63→}\\n    64→```\\n    65→\\n    66→The `capabilities` object determines which optional subcommands the CLI will call. If a capability is `false` or missing, the CLI will never invoke the corresponding subcommands.\\n    67→\\n    68→#### `detect`\\n    69→\\n    70→Checks whether the agent is present/usable in the current environment.\\n    71→\\n    72→**Arguments:** None\\n    73→\\n    74→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n    75→\\n    76→```json\\n    77→{\\\"present\\\": true}\\n    78→```\\n    79→\\n    80→#### `get-session-id`\\n    81→\\n    82→Extracts the session ID from a hook input event.\\n    83→\\n    84→**Input (stdin):** JSON — the HookInput object\\n    85→\\n    86→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n    87→\\n    88→```json\\n    89→{\\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\"}\\n    90→```\\n    91→\\n    92→#### `get-session-dir --repo-path <path>`\\n    93→\\n    94→Returns the directory where agent sessions are stored.\\n    95→\\n    96→**Arguments:**\\n    97→- `--repo-path` — Absolute path to the repository\\n    98→\\n    99→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   100→\\n   101→```json\\n   102→{\\\"session_dir\\\": \\\"/path/to/sessions\\\"}\\n   103→```\\n   104→\\n   105→#### `resolve-session-file --session-dir <dir> --session-id <id>`\\n   106→\\n   107→Resolves the session file path from a session directory and ID.\\n   108→\\n   109→**Arguments:**\\n   110→- `--session-dir` — Session directory path\\n   111→- `--session-id` — Session identifier\\n   112→\\n   113→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   114→\\n   115→```json\\n   116→{\\\"session_file\\\": \\\"/path/to/session/file.jsonl\\\"}\\n   117→```\\n   118→\\n   119→#### `read-session`\\n   120→\\n   121→Reads session data from a hook input event.\\n   122→\\n   123→**Input (stdin):** JSON — the HookInput object\\n   124→\\n   125→**Output (stdout):** JSON — AgentSession object\\n   126→\\n   127→```json\\n   128→{\\n   129→  \\\"session_id\\\": \\\"abc123\\\",\\n   130→  \\\"session_file\\\": \\\"/path/to/file.jsonl\\\"\\n   131→}\\n   132→```\\n   133→\\n   134→#### `write-session`\\n   135→\\n   136→Writes/updates session data.\\n   137→\\n   138→**Input (stdin):** JSON — the AgentSession object\\n   139→\\n   140→**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n   141→\\n   142→#### `read-transcript --session-ref <path>`\\n   143→\\n   144→Reads a transcript file and returns its raw bytes.\\n   145→\\n   146→**Arguments:**\\n   147→- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n   148→\\n   149→**Output (stdout):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n   150→\\n   151→#### `chunk-transcript --max-size <n>`\\n   152→\\n   153→Splits a transcript into chunks for storage.\\n   154→\\n   155→**Input (stdin):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n   156→\\n   157→**Arguments:**\\n   158→- `--max-size` — Maximum chunk size in bytes\\n   159→\\n   160→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   161→\\n   162→```json\\n   163→{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"<base64-encoded-chunk>\\\", \\\"...\\\"]}\\n   164→```\\n   165→\\n   166→#### `reassemble-transcript`\\n   167→\\n   168→Reassembles transcript chunks back into a full transcript.\\n   169→\\n   170→**Input (stdin):** JSON\\n   171→\\n   172→```json\\n   173→{\\\"chunks\\\": [\\\"<base64-encoded-chunk>\\\", \\\"...\\\"]}\\n   174→```\\n   175→\\n   176→**Output (stdout):** Raw transcript bytes.\\n   177→\\n   178→#### `format-resume-command --session-id <id>`\\n   179→\\n   180→Returns the command a user can run to resume a session.\\n   181→\\n   182→**Arguments:**\\n   183→- `--session-id` — Session identifier\\n   184→\\n   185→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   186→\\n   187→```json\\n   188→{\\\"command\\\": \\\"cursor --resume abc123\\\"}\\n   189→```\\n   190→\\n   191→### Capability: `hooks`\\n   192→\\n   193→These subcommands are required when `capabilities.hooks` is `true`.\\n   194→\\n   195→#### `parse-hook --hook <name>`\\n   196→\\n   197→Parses a raw agent hook payload into a structured event.\\n   198→\\n   199→**Arguments:**\\n   200→- `--hook` — Hook name (e.g., \\\"stop\\\", \\\"session-start\\\")\\n   201→\\n   202→**Input (stdin):** Raw agent hook payload bytes.\\n   203→\\n   204→**Output (stdout):** JSON — the parsed event, or `null` if the payload is not relevant.\\n   205→\\n   206→#### `install-hooks [--local-dev] [--force]`\\n   207→\\n   208→Installs agent hooks for Entire integration.\\n   209→\\n   210→**Arguments:**\\n   211→- `--local-dev` — Use local development binary path (optional)\\n   212→- `--force` — Overwrite existing hooks (optional)\\n   213→\\n   214→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   215→\\n   216→```json\\n   217→{\\\"hooks_installed\\\": 3}\\n   218→```\\n   219→\\n   220→#### `uninstall-hooks`\\n   221→\\n   222→Removes installed agent hooks.\\n   223→\\n   224→**Arguments:** None\\n   225→\\n   226→**Output:** Exit 0 on success.\\n   227→\\n   228→#### `are-hooks-installed`\\n   229→\\n   230→Checks whether hooks are currently installed.\\n   231→\\n   232→**Arguments:** None\\n   233→\\n   234→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   235→\\n   236→```json\\n   237→{\\\"installed\\\": true}\\n   238→```\\n   239→\\n   240→### Capability: `transcript_analyzer`\\n   241→\\n   242→Required when `capabilities.transcript_analyzer` is `true`.\\n   243→\\n   244→#### `get-transcript-position --path <path>`\\n   245→\\n   246→Returns the current byte position/size of a transcript file.\\n   247→\\n   248→**Arguments:**\\n   249→- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n   250→\\n   251→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   252→\\n   253→```json\\n   254→{\\\"position\\\": 12345}\\n   255→```\\n   256→\\n   257→#### `extract-modified-files --path <path> --offset <n>`\\n   258→\\n   259→Extracts the list of files modified by the agent from a transcript.\\n   260→\\n   261→**Arguments:**\\n   262→- `--path` — Path to the transcript file\\n   263→- `--offset` — Byte offset to start reading from\\n   264→\\n   265→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   266→\\n   267→```json\\n   268→{\\\"files\\\": [\\\"path/to/file1.go\\\", \\\"path/to/file2.go\\\"]}\\n   269→```\\n   270→\\n   271→#### `extract-prompts --session-ref <path> --offset <n>`\\n   272→\\n   273→Extracts user prompts from a transcript.\\n   274→\\n   275→**Arguments:**\\n   276→- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n   277→- `--offset` — Byte offset to start reading from\\n   278→\\n   279→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   280→\\n   281→```json\\n   282→{\\\"prompts\\\": [\\\"first prompt text\\\", \\\"second prompt text\\\"]}\\n   283→```\\n   284→\\n   285→#### `extract-summary --session-ref <path>`\\n   286→\\n   287→Extracts an AI-generated summary from a transcript.\\n   288→\\n   289→**Arguments:**\\n   290→- `--session-ref` — Path to the transcript file\\n   291→\\n   292→**Output (stdout):** JSON\\n   293→\\n   294→```json\\n   295→{\\\"summary\\\": \\\"Summary text here\\\", \\\"has